			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Spell Awareness Leadership<a name="49720"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 11:09 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I'm not trying to play down anyone else's experience, but personally, I've never had a trash mob for a raid I am leading surprise me with a spell I didn't expect.  Raids are planned events that I have researched thoroughly.  So in Ferubi, I know before going in that the Ukuns are going to try to snare me, that Chaos Claws are going to come from almost every pull in some form, that Anueks have a different snare, etc.  Spell awareness isn't going to help me prepare for those.  All it does it tell me when they're being cast, as expected.  Maybe other people pull raids without studying the zone first -- I don't do that.  I DO explore with a single group in new and different content and I totally agree Spell Awareness can come in handy there.  Raids aren't like that for me -- I take preparation very seriously and know in advance what I am going to face.  I tend to think of a raid situation as completely different from bouncing around with an XP group and I just don't see the value of spell awareness in the first case but do in the second.  But if you raid in zones without studying the mobs and what they're capable of casting before you plan the raid, then I guess it could be handy.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
