				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Spell Awareness Leadership<a name="50961"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 9 04 1:48 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;...spell awareness doesn't reveal boss spells that aren't player castable &quot;
<br />

<br />
It doesn't? The only ones I don't see are procs. 
<br />

<br />
Since bellow has an 18sec refresh, knowing exactly when &quot;MobX starts casting &lt;Gate&gt;&quot; so I can get the most out of my stun, has made this ability worth the price in and of itself. Especially when the gater will bring all the friends you extracted him from earlier. Or start summoning.
<br />

<br />
The big advantage when pulling is that there are times you have proximity aggro but are too far away to see the emotes from the mob and since they're casting you don't see them move. Or you've got aggro from behind a door. I see the spell awareness casting message (which is specific, not mobx starts to cast and it might be a buff) and know to start back pedalling.
<br />

<br />
The Ukun chains is a good expample of Spell Awarenss to save your life. In Vxed, on the right path after the first turn are two spawns side by side either of which can be an ukun. They are just over a crest. You try to play the server tick game to start your cast, but as you back off you see ukun chains (no you won't see an emote). You can fade before the spell hits, not after it lands and the see invis mob is on top of you. Otherwise you pull with Veeshans up and pray you resist.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
